<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for_each_linux_bus(lbus) macro likely expands to a for loop that iterates a global linked list (e.g. using a list head/next pointers) and thus its condition/increment clauses depend on list pointers or the list head. The body calls metal_linux_probe_bus(lbus), which can call metal_linux_bus_close(&lbus->bus) and remove/modify entries in that list. Therefore the second/third clauses of the expanded for loop would be using objects (the list head/next pointers) that are modified by the loop body (including via called functions), violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 (clauses 2 and/or 3).
</scenario>

